from michael d walker subject re on capital punishment randal lee nichola mandock write regarding the new draft of the universal catechism in procure the common good of society the need could arise that the aggressor be place in the position where he can not cause harm by virtue of thi the right and obligation of public authority to punish with proportionate penalty include the death penalty be acknowledge to the degree that mean other than the death penalty and military operation be sufficient to keep the peace then these non-violent provision be to be prefer because they be more in proportion and in keep with the final goal of protection of peace and human dignity exactly read that one sentence in there to the degree that mean other than the death penalty and military operation be sufficient to keep the peace then these non-violent provision be to be prefer i do believe that it be necessary for u to murder criminal to keep the peace the church in the united state feel the same way thu the reason that the catholic church ha oppose every execution in thi country in recent memory a be clearly show by thi excerpt the church teach on capital punishment remain today a it ha alway be in the past in total accord with my sentiment that i do not disagree with the use of deadly force in those case for which thi option be justifiable so what be justifiable a you state very explicitly from the new catechism the only justifiable case be when it be necessary to keep the peace since that do not apply at all to thi country the logical conclusion base on ymy own premise be that one must be oppose to any form of capital punishment in america just my opinion mike walker univ of illinoi 